## Task Lifecycle / Chat Message Data Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  participant Browser
  participant LiveView as ChatLive (LiveView)
  participant Chat as Platform.Chat
  participant DB as Postgres
  participant PubSub as Phoenix.PubSub
  participant Attention as AttentionRouter
  participant FS as Local Filesystem

  Browser->>LiveView: phx-submit "send" (content, attachments)
  LiveView->>Chat: Chat.Message.send_message(space_id, participant_id, attrs)
  Chat->>DB: INSERT chat_messages
  DB-->>Chat: message record
  Chat->>PubSub: broadcast {:new_message, message}
  PubSub-->>LiveView: {:new_message, message} (stream_insert)
  LiveView-->>Browser: push_event → auto-scroll

  Note over Attention: Telemetry :message_posted triggers AttentionRouter
  Attention->>DB: SELECT participants WHERE space_id = space
  Attention->>Attention: filter by attention_mode\n(active/mention/heartbeat)
  Attention->>PubSub: broadcast {:attention_needed, ...} (mention/active)

  Note over LiveView: File attachment upload path
  Browser->>LiveView: phx-change "validate" (upload preview)
  Browser->>LiveView: consume_uploaded_entries
  LiveView->>Chat: Chat.Attachment.upload(message_id, file_params)
  Chat->>FS: write to attachments/YYYY/MM/{uuid}_{filename}
  Chat->>DB: INSERT chat_attachments
  DB-->>Chat: attachment record
  Chat-->>LiveView: {:ok, attachment}
```

